The paper deals with the Feedback Vertex Set problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and is closely related to many other problems in computer science. The techniques used in the paper are primarily algorithmic and combinatorial, involving topics such as iterative compression, randomized branching, and cut-and-count. These topics are typically studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), graph theory (cs.GT), and computational geometry (cs.CG). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
